  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What are the most advanced car tools that people don't know about yet?",
  "response": "The automotive industry is continuously evolving, and with advancements in technology, there are some highly advanced car tools and systems that many people may not be aware of yet. Here are a few:\n\n### 1. **Augmented Reality (AR) Repair Guides**\n   - **What it is:** AR repair guides overlay digital instructions onto the real world through smart glasses or a smartphone camera. Mechanics can see step-by-step repair instructions directly on the vehicle they\u2019re working on.\n   - **Why it\u2019s advanced:** This tool can significantly reduce the time spent on repairs and improve accuracy, especially for complex tasks.\n\n### 2. **AI-Powered Diagnostic Tools**\n   - **What it is:** These tools use artificial intelligence to diagnose car problems by analyzing data from the car\u2019s sensors and systems. They can predict potential failures before they happen.\n   - **Why it\u2019s advanced:** AI diagnostics can provide more accurate and faster diagnostics than traditional OBD (On-Board Diagnostics) tools, potentially saving time and money.\n\n### 3. **3D Printing for Custom Parts**\n   - **What it is:** 3D printers are being used to create custom or hard-to-find car parts on demand. This can be especially useful for older or rare vehicles.\n   - **Why it\u2019s advanced:** 3D printing allows for rapid prototyping and production of parts, reducing the need for extensive inventories and lowering costs.\n\n### 4. **Advanced Driver-Assistance Systems (ADAS) Calibration Tools**\n   - **What it is:** These tools are used to calibrate ADAS features like lane-keeping assist, adaptive cruise control, and automatic emergency braking after repairs or windshield replacements.\n   - **Why it\u2019s advanced:** Proper calibration is crucial for the safety and functionality of ADAS, and these tools ensure that the systems operate correctly.\n\n### 5. **Wireless Charging for Electric Vehicles (EVs)**\n   - **What it is:** Wireless charging systems for EVs use inductive charging to power up the vehicle without the need for physical plugs.\n   - **Why it\u2019s advanced:** This technology can make charging more convenient and could be integrated into roads for dynamic charging while driving.\n\n### 6. **Predictive Maintenance Systems**\n   - **What it is:** These systems use data from sensors and machine learning algorithms to predict when certain parts of the car will need maintenance or replacement.\n   - **Why it\u2019s advanced:** Predictive maintenance can prevent breakdowns and extend the lifespan of vehicle components, saving money in the long run.\n\n### 7. **Smart Body Repair Tools**\n   - **What it is:** These tools use lasers, sensors, and software to measure and repair car body damage with precision.\n   - **Why it\u2019s advanced:** They can reduce the time and cost of body repairs while improving the accuracy and quality of the work.\n\n### 8. **Automotive Cybersecurity Tools**\n   - **What it is:** As cars become more connected, cybersecurity tools are being developed to protect vehicles from hacking and unauthorized access.\n   - **Why it\u2019s advanced:** These tools are essential for ensuring the safety and privacy of drivers as cars become more integrated with the internet and other smart devices.\n\n### 9. **Holographic Displays for Mechanics**\n   - **What it is:** Holographic displays can project 3D images of car components, allowing mechanics to visualize and interact with them in a more intuitive way.\n   - **Why it\u2019s advanced:** This technology can enhance understanding and efficiency in complex repairs.\n\n### 10. **Self-Healing Materials**\n   - **What it is:** Some advanced materials can repair themselves when damaged, such as scratches on paint or cracks in certain components.\n   - **Why it\u2019s advanced:** Self-healing materials can reduce the need for repairs and maintenance, lowering long-term costs.\n\nThese tools and technologies are still emerging and may not be widely known or used yet, but they represent the future of automotive maintenance and repair. As they become more accessible, they could revolutionize how we care for and interact with our vehicles.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
